The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Aug. 7: The government has decided to retain the threshold of 5,000 hectares for a special economic zone, virtually dashing big developers hopes of revision in the land ceiling on SEZs. The empowered group of ministers, headed by external affairs minister Pranab Mukherjee, took up operational issues such as inter-ministry differences on service tax exemptions to the units in SEZs.                            
	 Mumbai, Aug. 7: Tata Steel has identified raw material resources in America, Africa and Australia for acquisition to ensure that 50 per cent of the requirement of Corus is met through captive sources.                             
	 London, Aug. 7: ArcelorMittal will invest $1.6 billion to enhance its crude steel production capacity in Brazil. The company will expand its production capacity to 6.5 million tonnes from 3.9 million at present.                            
	 Mumbai, Aug. 7: Four major public sector lenders including the Bank of India and Corporation Bank have raised their benchmark lending rates by up to 0.75 per cent as a fallout of the further tightening of monetary policy by the RBI.                            
	 Mumbai, Aug 7: Bombay High Court has directed the postponement of the AGM of Zandu Pharmaceuticals due on August 9 amid controversy over a takeover bid by Emami Ltd.                                                                                                                                             
